class.name: System.Diagnostics.TraceListenerCollection
class.summary: Provides a list of TraceListener objects.

property.name: Count
property.summary: Returns the number of items in the list.

property.name: Item(System.String)
property.summary: Gets the first TraceListener in the list with the specified name.

method.name: GetEnumerator
method.summary: Returns an enumerator for the list of listeners.

method.name: RemoveAt(System.Int32)
method.summary: Removes the listener at the specified index.
method.param: Location of the listener to remove.

method.name: Clear
method.summary: Clears all listeners from the list.

method.name: Add(System.Diagnostics.TraceListener)
method.summary: Adds a TraceListener to the list.
method.param: The being added to the list.
method.returns: The position in the list where the listener was inserted.

method.name: AddRange(System.Diagnostics.TraceListener[])
method.summary: Adds an array of s to the list.
method.param: Array of to add to the list.

method.name: AddRange(System.Diagnostics.TraceListenerCollection)
method.summary: Adds the contents of another TraceListenerCollection to this one.
method.param: The TraceListenerCollection to copy values from.

method.name: Contains(System.Diagnostics.TraceListener)
method.summary: Checks to see if the list contains the specified listener.
method.returns: true if list contains listener; false otherwise.

method.name: CopyTo(System.Diagnostics.TraceListener[], System.Int32)
method.summary: Copies a section of the current TraceListenerCollection to the specified array at the specified index.

method.name: IndexOf(System.Diagnostics.TraceListener)
method.summary: Gets the index of the specified listener.
method.returns: The index of the listener in the list, if it exists.

method.name: Insert(System.Int32, System.Diagnostics.TraceListener)
method.summary: Inserts the specified listener into the list at the specified index.
method.param: Location in the list to insert the listener.
The TraceListener to insert into the list.

method.name: Remove(System.String)
method.summary: Removes the listener with the specified name from the list, if it exists.

method.name: Remove(System.Diagnostics.TraceListener)
method.summary: Removes the specified listener from the list.
